         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">June 9th [189]5 ¶ Dear Baron ¶  ¶ While collecting in the Eumundi ¶  scrub the other day I met with for the first time, a raceme of ripe fruit of your Helicia glabriflora and find it will have to be p...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">95.06.09</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Frederick Bailey</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Letter press copy book 3, p. 101, Queensland Herbarium, Brisbane.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">June 9th [189]5<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">editorial addition.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Baron</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>While collecting in the Eumundi<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Qld.</p>
               </note> scrub the other day I met with for the first time, a raceme of ripe fruit of your <name key="Helicia%20glabriflora">Helicia glabriflora</name> and find it will have to be placed in my Cyanocarpus. There will be no occasion however to alter the specific name. I point this out to you as in any publication where you may speak of the plant it will be well to mention it henceforth as <name key="Cyanocarpus%20glabriflorus">Cyanocarpus glabriflorus</name>.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>No record of Bailey publishing this name has been found; he used <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Helecia glabriflora</seg> in Bailey (1899-1905), <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>p. 1328.</p>
               </note> Hoping your health continues good I am always yours very truly,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">F. Manson Bailey</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">short description of fruit</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>A drupe form — oblong, about ½ in. long, of a glossy dark blue colour epicarp fleshy and juicy blue like the outside, endocarp chartaceous. Embryo minute Ripe June Hab. Eumundi.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Cyanocarpus%20glabriflorus">Cyanocarpus glabriflorus</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Helicia%20glabriflora">Helicia glabriflora</name>
            </p>
         </div>
